summary: This is an FBI interview report (FD-302) documenting the interview of Julio Cesar Suarez on November 4, 2009. Suarez was interviewed in Boca Raton, Florida, regarding his travel with his friend Alfredo Rodriguez to the Hilton Hotel, where Rodriguez was delivering unspecified documents. The report details Suarez's limited knowledge of the documents and his receipt of Rodriguez's vehicle at the conclusion of the interview.

events.title: FBI Interview of Julio Cesar Suarez
events.description: FBI agents interviewed Julio Cesar Suarez in the vicinity of the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton, Florida. He was advised of his rights and provided information about traveling with Alfredo Rodriguez, who was delivering documents to the hotel.

locations: Hilton Hotel, 7920 Glades Road, Boca Raton, Florida
El Cristo restaurant, 8th Street, Miami, Florida
keyFacts: Alfredo Rodriguez traveled to the Hilton Hotel in Boca Raton to deliver unspecified documents, accompanied by his friend Julio Cesar Suarez.
Suarez denied having any knowledge of what the documents Rodriguez brought were related to.
At the conclusion of the interview, Rodriguez's Chevrolet Trailblazer was released to Suarez at Rodriguez's request.
Rodriguez rents the El Cristo restaurant in Miami and was previously employed at another restaurant.
The interview was conducted under a formal FD-395 Advice of Rights procedure, which Suarez understood and signed.
